<header>

	<div class="container">

		<h2>Typography</h2>

		<p>
			The typographic grid included in Watercolor establishes a vertical baseline for all text on the site, and takes most of the pain out of making your text content look great. Just set the <code>$line-height</code> variable and all of the hard work is taken care of for you, allowing you to focus on organizing your content rather than working with text styles.
		</p>

	</div>

</header>

<section id="typographic-settings">

    <div class="container">

		<h3>Typographic Settings</h3>

		<p>Line height and other typographic settings are defined in <a href="/overview#global">global.scss</a> and are the basis for the typographic grid.  By default the base font size is set at<code>100</code> percent, or 16 pixels, and the line height is set as a close to golden-ratio <code>1.625</code>.</p>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th style="width: 25%">variable</th>
					<th>description</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$line-height</code></td>
					<td>This defines the height of one line of text. This is useful for maintaining vertical rhythm when applying margin or padding to elements, or for standardizing the height of elements. Default value: <code>1.625</code>.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

    </div>

</section>

<section id="mixins">

    <div class="container">

		<h3>Typographic Mixins</h3>

		<p>The typographic @@mixins are defined in <a href="/overview#grid">grid.scss</a> and provide @@mixins for setting font sizes, margins, and line heights to fit the typographic baseline grid.</p>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th style="width: 25%">mixin</th>
					<th>description</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><code>font-size($size)</code></td>
					<td>This is a composite @@mixin that will set the font size, line height, and top/bottom margins all at once, provided the desired font size.</td>
				</tr>
					<tr>
					<td><code>font-line-height($size)</code></td>
					<td>This @@mixin will set the line height, given the font size, allowing it to fit the typographic baseline grid.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>font-margin-top($size, $adjust)</code></td>
					<td>This @@mixin will set the top margin, given the font size and an optional adjustment value, allowing it to fit the typographic baseline grid. The adjustment value is where you would input an adjustment amount, so the margin is reduced, for example, by the border size on the element. The <code>$adjust</code> parameter defaults to a value of <code>0</code> if it is not provided.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>font-margin-bottom($size, $adjust)</code></td>
					<td>This @@mixin will set the bottom margin, given the font size and an optional adjustment value, allowing it to fit the typographic baseline grid. The adjustment value is where you would input an adjustment amount, so the margin is reduced, for example, by the border size on the element. The <code>$adjust</code> parameter defaults to a value of <code>0</code> if it is not provided.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

    </div>

</section>

<section id="text-body">

    <div class="container">

		<h3>Body Text</h3>
		<p>Body text is defaulted to 100% font size, with a 1.625 &mdash; close-to-golden-ratio &mdash; line height.  The entire typographical grid is based on this line height, which will help your site keep a consistent vertical rhythm.</p>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th style="width: 25%">variable</th>
					<th>description</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$body-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size of body text in ems. Default value: <code>1</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$body-font-color</code></td>
					<td>Color of body text. Default value: <code>#6e787b</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$body-font-family</code></td>
					<td>Font family stack used for body text. Default value: <code>'Roboto', sans-serif</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$body-font-weight</code></td>
					<td>Font weight used for body text. Default value: <code>300</code>.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

		<div class="example">

			<p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat. Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat.</p>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;p&gt;
   Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat. Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat.
&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

    </div>

</section>

<section id="text-headers">

    <div class="container">

		<h3>Headings</h3>
		<p>Headings are set in progressively larger sizes. Each is given one line of margin above the header, while the header is centered within as few lines as possible. Note that the default <code>h1</code> header takes three lines with one line of margin on top of bottom, while the <code>h2</code> can fit within two lines with one line of margin on top of bottom. The calculations to make this work are handled within Watercolor automatically, all you need to do is set the header font size and it will be set up to look great.</p>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th style="width: 25%">variable</th>
					<th>description</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$h1-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size of h1 header text in ems. Default value: <code>3.4375</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$h2-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size of h2 header text in ems. Default value: <code>2.625</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$h3-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size of h3 header text in ems. Default value: <code>2.125</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$h4-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size of h4 header text in ems. Default value: <code>1.625</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$h5-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size of h5 header text in ems. Default value: <code>1.3125</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$h6-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size of h6 header text in ems. Default value: <code>1</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$header-font-color</code></td>
					<td>Color of header text. Default value: <code>#6e787b</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$header-font-family</code></td>
					<td>Font family stack used for header text. Default value: <code>'Roboto', sans-serif</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$header-font-weight</code></td>
					<td>Font weight used for header text. Default value: <code>100</code>.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

		<div class="example">

			<h1>Header 1</h1>
			<h2>Header 2</h2>
			<h3>Header 3</h3>
			<h4>Header 4</h4>
			<h5>Header 5</h5>
			<h6>Header 6</h6>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;h1&gt;Header 1&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Header 2&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Header 3&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Header 4&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h5&gt;Header 5&lt;/h5&gt;
&lt;h6&gt;Header 6&lt;/h6&gt;</code></pre>

    </div>

</section>

<section id="preformatted">

    <div class="container">

		<h3>Preformatted Text</h3>
		<p>Preformatted, or monospaced, text should be enclosed in <code>&lt;pre&gt;</code> tags. Block code should be enclosed in <code>&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;</code> tags.</p>

		<table class="bordered">

			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th style="width: 25%">variable</th>
					<th>description</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>

			<tbody>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$mono-font-size</code></td>
					<td>Size monospaced text, used in elements such as <code>pre</code> and <code>code</code>,in ems. Default value: <code>1</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$mono-font-color</code></td>
					<td>Color of monospaced text, used in elements such as <code>pre</code> and <code>code</code>. Default value: <code>#6e787b</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$mono-font-family</code></td>
					<td>Font family stack used for monospaced text. Default value: <code>monospace, sans-serif</code>.</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td><code>$mono-font-weight</code></td>
					<td>Font weight used for monospaced text. Default value: <code>normal</code>.</td>
				</tr>
			</tbody>

		</table>

		<div class="example">

			<pre>Lorem ipsum
dolor sit amet
consectetuer adipiscing elit</pre>
			<pre><code>code {
   color: rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
   text-shadow: none;
   border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
   background-color: transparent;
   vertical-align: middle;
}</code></pre>

		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;pre&gt;Lorem ipsum
dolor sit amet
consectetuer adipiscing elit&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;code {
   color: rgba(0,0,0,0.15);
   text-shadow: none;
   border: 1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
   background-color: transparent;
   vertical-align: middle;
}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;</code></pre>

    </div>

</section>

<section id="blockquotes">

    <div class="container">

		<h3>Blockquotes</h3>
		<p>Blockquotes are pulled to the right of the main text. Watercolor gives them slightly further distinction with a vertical left border that is common practice to better separate the quote from surrounding text.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<p>A quick quote from lorem ipsum:</p>
			<blockquote>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat. Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat.</blockquote>
			<p>Now that we're done with that lets move on.</p>
		</div>

		<pre class="example-code"><code class="language-markup">&lt;p&gt;A quick quote from lorem ipsum:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
   Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat.
   Ut wisi enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exerci tation ullamcorper suscipit lobortis nisl ut aliquip ex ea commodo consequat.
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now that we're done with that lets move on.&lt;/p&gt;</code></pre>

    </div>

</section>

<section id="inline-text">

    <div class="container">

		<h3>Inline Text</h3>
		<p>All inline text is styled to perserve vertical rhythm and give a consistent visual look across your site.</p>

		<div class="example">

			<p class="fifty-percent">
				<a href="#">anchor link</a><br>
				<abbr title="abbreviation title">abbreviation</abbr><br>
				<b>bold text</b><br>
				<cite>citation</cite><br>
				<code>.code {visibility: hidden;}</code><br>
				<del>deleted text</del><br>
				<dfn title="definition term title">definition term</dfn><br>
				<em>emphasisted text</em><br>
				<i>alternate voice</i><br>
				<ins>inserted text</ins><br>
				<kbd>keyboard input text</kbd><br>
			</p>

			<p class="fifty-percent">
				<mark>marked text</mark><br>
				<q>short <q>quotation inside</q> of another quotation</q><br>
				<s>incorrect text</s><br>
				<samp>sample text</samp><br>
				<small>small text</small><br>
				<span>span text</span><br>
				<strong>strong text</strong><br>
				<sub>subscript text</sub><br>
				<sup>superscript text</sup><br>
				<u>underlined text</u><br>
				<var>variable</var>
			</p>

		</div>

